WEBVTT

00:00.034 --> 00:03.678
The following message by Alistair Begg is made available by Truth For Life.

00:04.499 --> 00:08.463
For more information, visit us online at truthforlife.org.

00:11.006 --> 00:22.859
I invite you, if you're able, to turn to the Book of Romans and to chapter 8 and to follow along as I read in a moment to the first eight verses.

00:23.720 --> 00:28.946
Now, I had to decide that there was something that I would say

00:29.122 --> 00:37.590
over these addresses, and I thought that I would like to stay in something that would be progressive as we studied it.

00:38.451 --> 00:51.203
And I know that you believe that all Scripture is equally inspired, but not every passage of Scripture is equally inspiring.

00:52.103 --> 00:59.090
And that is why, and you can check this on your own later on, that is why we're not going to launch into first chronicles.

00:59.586 --> 01:05.015
And we are going to make an attempt, at least, in Romans 8.

01:06.217 --> 01:07.699
So you can read it for homework.

01:07.719 --> 01:09.282
You can plan ahead.

01:09.803 --> 01:13.629
It's very rich, and we'll have to be somewhat selective as we go.

01:13.649 --> 01:23.906
But nevertheless, we trust that the Spirit of God, using the Word of God, will do the work of God in each of our lives.

01:24.807 --> 01:26.610
So Romans 8 and verse 1.

01:27.906 --> 01:33.212
There is, therefore, now no condemnation for those who are in Christ Jesus.

01:34.214 --> 01:40.641
For the law of the spirit of life has set you free in Christ Jesus from the law of sin and death.

01:41.863 --> 01:45.707
For God has done what the law weakened by the flesh could not do.

01:46.629 --> 01:57.842
By sending his own son in the likeness of sinful flesh and for sin, he condemned sin in the flesh in order that the righteous requirement of the law

01:58.082 --> 02:04.570
might be fulfilled in us, who walk not according to the flesh, but according to the Spirit.

02:05.751 --> 02:16.044
For those who live according to the flesh set their minds on the things of the flesh, but those who live according to the Spirit set their minds on the things of the Spirit.

02:17.385 --> 02:24.754
For to set the mind on the flesh is death, but to set the mind on the Spirit is life and peace.

02:25.954 --> 02:32.843
For the mind that is said on the flesh is hostile to God, but it does not submit to God's law.

02:33.604 --> 02:34.766
Indeed, it cannot.

02:35.907 --> 02:39.753
Those who are in the flesh cannot please God.

02:41.876 --> 02:43.318
This is the word of the Lord.

02:46.422 --> 02:49.266
Just checking on any present Anglicans.

02:53.091 --> 02:53.591
There we go.

02:53.652 --> 02:54.052
Thank you.

02:54.112 --> 02:54.633
There we go.

02:54.713 --> 02:55.474
That's right.

02:55.842 --> 03:01.590
All the Baptists are wondering exactly what that is, but just ask around.

03:01.630 --> 03:03.312
You'll be fine.

03:03.332 --> 03:05.335
Let's have a brief prayer together.

03:05.395 --> 03:14.547
Father, how we thank you for the privilege to assemble in freedom in this place on this occasion in the company of one another.

03:15.288 --> 03:17.091
And we thank you that we gather to you.

03:17.111 --> 03:22.278
We look from ourselves to your Word to Christ, the living Word.

03:22.919 --> 03:25.522
And we pray that your Word might

03:25.954 --> 03:37.406
plant itself afresh in our hearts even as we ponder the vastness of all that Paul has said here by the Holy Spirit in the book of Romans itself.

03:38.207 --> 03:50.721
To this end we seek you and we humbly anticipate that you being such a good and gracious God will match the feeble words of a small individual.

03:52.263 --> 03:55.506
Be in the voice piece of your living truth.

03:56.066 --> 04:01.912
to the individual needs of each of our lives this afternoon as we come in Christ's name.

04:02.652 --> 04:03.013
Amen.

04:05.235 --> 04:18.848
Well, of course, one of the reasons that I thought it would be nice to do Romans 8 is because it is such a comprehensive statement beginning with no condemnation and ending with no separation.

04:19.809 --> 04:25.074
In the 17th century, Thomas Jakum said of Romans 8,

04:25.538 --> 04:35.593
From first to last, it is high gospel, and it is all gospel, its matter being entirely evangelical.

04:37.095 --> 04:41.141
I would imagine that most of us here are familiar with the notion of the gospel.

04:41.161 --> 04:46.349
We understand it's the good news of all that God has done for us in Christ.

04:47.310 --> 04:49.874
But it is, at this point in history,

04:50.146 --> 04:56.553
Even as Jacob in the 17th century says, this is at heart evangelical.

04:56.973 --> 05:02.900
In other words, it is pressing upon people the claims of Christ and the need to respond to Christ.

05:03.721 --> 05:19.698
And if the church is going to be equipped in doing that well, it is a vital importance that each of us has a deep-seated conviction about the truth, the relevance, and the power of the gospel.

05:20.066 --> 05:24.371
about its truth, about its relevance, and about its power.

05:25.752 --> 05:39.188
We're not free to design a gospel of our own contriving, a story that somehow or another is acceptable to a compromised church or in a confused culture.

05:40.008 --> 05:48.498
Augustine said, a long time ago, if we choose only to believe what we want to believe about the gospel,

05:48.738 --> 05:54.764
and reject the rest, it is not the gospel we actually believe it is ourselves.

05:55.985 --> 06:10.859
And the world in which we live at various stages and in a variety of places, most of us in the Western world, is without question fascinated by spiritual things and at the same time amazingly confused.

06:11.800 --> 06:18.386
I have just come across a Spanish singer, I came across it by reading the London Times,

06:18.466 --> 06:27.976
I think her name is Rosalia, and her latest album has been covered by tremendous interest in the media.

06:28.317 --> 06:39.609
And she obviously, as somebody of great influence, combining the journalists say an interest in spirituality with techno music and with classical instrumentation and so on.

06:40.490 --> 06:48.018
And I looked her up and she announced the fact that she is interested in a spirituality

06:48.098 --> 06:52.645
that lives in doubt as much as it lives in certainty.

06:53.666 --> 07:00.276
I, she said, resonate with Buddhism, Islam, Christianity, Hinduism.

07:00.316 --> 07:03.821
All have things I can relate to.

07:03.841 --> 07:08.648
They broaden my ideas of spirituality.

07:08.688 --> 07:15.538
And that I think is not a surprise to us because we live in a time when it's okay to be seeking

07:15.778 --> 07:18.101
It's just not okay to be finding.

07:18.842 --> 07:20.564
It's not okay to be concluding.

07:21.626 --> 07:28.535
It is a time where the implications of a cultural malaise are obvious for all to see.

07:28.575 --> 07:36.786
I've been saying this everywhere for ages now, but our young people, students in particular, are living with three great lies.

07:37.668 --> 07:40.692
Lie one that there is no personal creator, God.

07:41.252 --> 07:45.458
Lie two that there is no absolute morality.

07:45.666 --> 07:48.569
and lie through that there is no ultimate truth.

07:49.410 --> 08:14.418
And if that is the time frame in which they live, and if that is the kind of consensus worldview that they're tempted to embrace, then for us to go out into the thoroughfares of life, whether they are with our neighbors or our friends or our colleagues or our business associates or our grandchildren, we realize that if we're going to hold true to the truth, the relevance and the power of the gospel,

08:14.594 --> 08:20.642
It cannot be some kind of harmlessly accommodating vague theological tripe.

08:21.323 --> 08:27.211
We are stuck with the message as presented to us and given us in Jesus.

08:27.952 --> 08:34.421
My next door neighbor, our next door neighbor in Solon for a long time was a Jewish cardiologist at the clinic.

08:34.441 --> 08:38.085
A wonderful man I liked him very much, his name was Fred.

08:38.105 --> 08:41.490
And he wanted me dreadfully to become a Unitarian.

08:41.922 --> 08:48.230
Because he said, we will get on far better if you can just lose the Jesus part.

08:49.171 --> 08:55.338
And I told him, listen, first of all, Fred, you need to know that Jesus is the Messiah who came for you.

08:56.019 --> 08:59.484
But secondly, you say he isn't the Messiah, and I say he is.

08:59.924 --> 09:01.186
We can't both be right.

09:02.908 --> 09:09.436
And Islam says that we can outweigh our bad with our good.

09:09.536 --> 09:11.218
That's why they have skills.

09:11.650 --> 09:17.937
We have a cross because we say, no, we could never outlive our bad or outbid it.

09:18.618 --> 09:19.659
We need a Savior.

09:20.660 --> 09:21.821
We can't both be right.

09:23.063 --> 09:30.751
And so we have to recognize that what we are dealing with when we turn to the Scripture is the inerring Word of God.

09:30.931 --> 09:36.237
And it is here as it begins in verse 8 and verse 1, with therefore.

09:37.739 --> 09:40.562
Paul has been writing now some seven chapters.

09:40.674 --> 09:46.306
and he has been dealing with the reality of life before a Holy God.

09:46.987 --> 09:50.194
In short order, the story that he's been proclaiming is this.

09:51.777 --> 09:58.150
God made us, God made the world, we broke it, Jesus fixed it.

09:58.832 --> 10:01.778
God made it, we broke it, Jesus fixed it.

10:02.018 --> 10:16.416
And the predicament that is conveyed there in those early chapters, particularly chapter one, behind a facade of wisdom, we've been intrigued by all kinds of things and refused to give glory to God, and we pretend and worship various things.

10:16.957 --> 10:19.360
And he says, there is no hope in that at all.

10:19.961 --> 10:22.224
No hope either if you're a religious person.

10:22.244 --> 10:30.194
He goes into chapter two, and in chapter three, he hits the high spot, and he says, the whole world is held accountable before God.

10:30.498 --> 10:36.245
And from there, he moves on to the reality of all of the provision that has been made in Jesus.

10:36.305 --> 10:43.433
So I take it when he says, therefore, he is referring to all that he has already proclaimed.

10:43.994 --> 10:49.080
It may be particularly in chapter seven and chapter six, but nevertheless, it all fits.

10:49.340 --> 10:50.181
What is he saying?

10:50.482 --> 10:50.762
What?

10:51.163 --> 10:52.404
Therefore, what?

10:52.825 --> 10:55.568
Therefore, he says, there is no condemnation.

10:55.948 --> 10:57.330
There is no condemnation.

10:57.730 --> 11:09.083
Now, you need to go back and do your homework to realize that back in chapter 7, Paul has been articulating the fact that he is aware that he is a wretched man.

11:09.704 --> 11:11.126
He's a wretched man, he says.

11:11.486 --> 11:15.511
The good that I want to do, I don't do, and the bad that I don't want to do, I end up doing.

11:16.031 --> 11:18.635
Who will deliver me from this body of death?

11:19.275 --> 11:21.738
Well, that's about the 24th verse of chapter 7.

11:21.778 --> 11:25.042
And here we are, the first verse of chapter 8,

11:25.218 --> 11:30.247
And he says, there's therefore now no condemnation to them that are in Christ Jesus.

11:30.808 --> 11:32.010
So is this a contradiction?

11:32.030 --> 11:33.793
No, it's a paradox.

11:34.014 --> 11:35.116
It's not a contradiction.

11:35.997 --> 11:44.833
At Jim Packer years ago, the late Jim Packer, speaking in Glasgow, he used a wonderful illustration that helped me when I was young and I've never forgotten it.

11:45.374 --> 11:49.842
He said, if you think of the Christian life as being like a house, then

11:49.986 --> 12:02.301
If, depending on the way your house is situated on planet Earth, but if you are in the north side of the house where the sun is not penetrating, then it will be cool over there.

12:02.862 --> 12:05.345
And perhaps you wear a cardigan or something.

12:05.365 --> 12:12.113
When you go to the south side of the house, then the sun shines and you can enjoy the benefits of that.

12:13.194 --> 12:19.602
Both are a reality within the house, and he says, and both are true within the Christian life.

12:20.322 --> 12:26.749
And Romans chapter 7 is, if you like, the north side, where we're made aware of what we really are before God.

12:27.349 --> 12:42.886
And Romans chapter 8 takes us in to the south side to see to us even though we are what we are as redeemed sinners, being no doubt there is therefore now no condemnation to them that are in Christ Jesus.

12:42.906 --> 12:46.930
Every accusation that is hurled against us by the evil one,

12:47.170 --> 12:55.541
who loves to unsettle as an undoous and complain about the mess that we've made of our lives or the difficulties that we've had of some time.

12:56.182 --> 13:14.708
Our answer to that is to tell him to go back to where he belongs, because we have a sinless Savior who died, and as a result of that, my guilty soul is counted free for God the justice satisfied to look on Jesus and pardon me.

13:14.768 --> 13:16.530
And that's why there is now.

13:16.610 --> 13:17.692
no condemnation.

13:18.473 --> 13:42.689
Preaching on this a fellow in Scotland years ago, a long time ago, in a big church near the center of Edinburgh, was asked by an indignant member of his congregation who had been working his way verse by verse through the Book of Romans, and he came to the minister and he said, tell me minister, when will we get out of Romans chapter 7?

13:43.130 --> 13:45.714
And he said,

13:45.922 --> 13:50.248
As long as I'm your minister, you'll never get out of Romans chapter 7.

13:51.309 --> 14:06.149
And what he meant by that was he was rebutting the idea of a kind of higher life mentality that says there's a way to spring out of chapter 7 and live entirely in chapter 8.

14:07.050 --> 14:11.937
But that's neither true to the Bible nor is it true to human experience.

14:12.498 --> 14:15.762
And that's why it makes it such a wonderful thing

14:15.970 --> 14:19.116
to be immediately reminded of, what?

14:20.418 --> 14:23.063
When is there no condemnation?

14:23.483 --> 14:24.465
Answer, now.

14:25.367 --> 14:26.248
Well, where'd you get that?

14:26.288 --> 14:27.851
Well, it's right in the sentence.

14:27.871 --> 14:30.716
There is therefore now no condemnation.

14:31.738 --> 14:35.665
It's not a possibility held out in the future.

14:35.705 --> 14:40.754
It is a reality to be enjoyed as a present certainty.

14:41.378 --> 14:53.680
This is not a new element in Paul's work here, because remember, in Romans chapter 5, he said, therefore, by the grace of God, we have peace with God.

14:53.700 --> 14:59.610
Therefore, being justified by faith, we have peace with God in which we now stand.

15:00.572 --> 15:04.178
And this, you see, is the remarkable thing about the gospel.

15:04.738 --> 15:07.541
And some of you have already been in some of these cathedrals.

15:07.682 --> 15:19.436
Even today, I went into one small place, cost me 150 euros, which is a Scotsman, is a very big stretch, I have to tell you.

15:20.097 --> 15:26.225
I don't really know why I did it in the end, but I was embarrassed into it.

15:26.245 --> 15:33.714
Anyway, and I went in and I took a few photographs, and there was a large Mary holding a little Jesus.

15:35.330 --> 15:42.820
as if some are another, that Mary would be able to intercede when we couldn't get through to Jesus.

15:44.002 --> 15:46.585
She could put in a good word for us.

15:48.027 --> 15:49.028
I don't know where you are.

15:49.088 --> 15:51.151
You may have come from a Roman Catholic background.

15:51.291 --> 16:00.444
If you have a deep conviction that there is no condemnation for those who are now in Christ Jesus, that is not because of your Roman Catholicism.

16:00.464 --> 16:03.488
That is only because of the truth of the gospel.

16:03.848 --> 16:05.170
And if you believe that,

16:05.410 --> 16:12.539
then you're kind of getting nice Protestant and you're a lousy Catholic, okay?

16:12.559 --> 16:16.043
Because that is not Roman Catholic doctrine.

16:16.584 --> 16:21.911
There is therefore now no condemnation to them that are in Christ Jesus.

16:22.612 --> 16:28.319
Augustus top lady who wrote the hymn Rock of Ages cleft for me, which is amazing hymn, isn't it?

16:28.919 --> 16:34.226
Remember, he says in that hymn, the glorified spirits in heaven

16:34.850 --> 16:38.293
may be happier, but they are no more secure.

16:40.155 --> 16:50.164
The glorified spirits of heaven, those of our loved ones who died in Christ and have been gathered to Him, may be happier than we are, but they are no more secure than we are.

16:50.805 --> 16:56.710
Because once in Christ, in Him forever, what no condemnation?

16:57.611 --> 16:59.953
When, now, for whom?

16:59.994 --> 17:03.597
For those who are in Christ Jesus.

17:04.097 --> 17:04.818
There you are.

17:04.898 --> 17:06.040
We made it through a verse.

17:06.861 --> 17:08.504
We've only got a while to go.

17:10.187 --> 17:11.991
You're going to say, I wish you'd stayed off the boat.

17:12.051 --> 17:13.613
We could have got on a lot faster.

17:13.673 --> 17:17.019
The peen got through many more verses than you've done.

17:17.821 --> 17:19.303
And I understand.

17:20.045 --> 17:24.432
But you know that Paul actually doesn't use Christian at all in his writings.

17:26.216 --> 17:29.842
He refers to the believer as being in Christ.

17:30.210 --> 17:41.205
Classically, perhaps, 2 Corinthians 5, if anyone is in Christ, is a new creation, the oldest gone, then you have come.

17:42.347 --> 17:44.149
So this is the real question, isn't it?

17:44.169 --> 17:50.638
I guess I'm going to refer to Scottish ministers this afternoon, because I have another one for you.

17:51.239 --> 17:52.581
And this was a friend of mine.

17:52.621 --> 17:53.763
He's now gone to heaven.

17:54.584 --> 17:58.930
At his funeral, he told, at his wife's funeral, he told the story.

17:59.106 --> 18:00.288
of how he met her.

18:01.269 --> 18:16.510
He met her walking out of a tennis court, and he was attracted to this girl, and as they walked, there was a Christian conference, and as they walked away, he said to her, and are you a believer?

18:16.570 --> 18:24.321
And she said, oh yes, I am in Christ since such and such a day.

18:24.701 --> 18:25.722
I am in Christ.

18:27.184 --> 18:28.306
And he said to himself,

18:28.898 --> 18:33.143
I have never heard anybody answer in that way.

18:33.764 --> 18:35.066
This is a special girl.

18:36.347 --> 18:48.282
And he said, and so her life was in Christ, lived for Christ, and now she is with Christ.

18:49.604 --> 18:52.127
But the progression is foundational.

18:53.008 --> 18:57.874
That's why Calvin said, all that Christ has done for us.

18:58.530 --> 19:08.400
in his atoning death on the cross is of no value to us so long as we remain outside of Christ.

19:09.761 --> 19:27.058
Now you see what Paul is doing here in this great theological treatise is urging upon us as his readers the necessity of not simply giving an assent to the identity or even the historicity or even the efficacy

19:27.170 --> 19:38.986
of who Christ is and what He's done, not simply giving a cent to it, but committing to it, making it our own, receiving all that He has done.

19:39.987 --> 19:47.957
And you may be here, and you've come with a friend, and you're wondering what you're getting yourself into, and even as you listen to me now, you're having to process this.

19:48.017 --> 19:48.899
