20:23.810 --> 20:27.756
Well, one answer to that is before the foundation of the world, I understand that.

20:29.899 --> 20:32.483
But becoming a Christian is a bit like getting married, you know.

20:32.523 --> 20:39.553
There's not a lot of feeling attached to it, not the actual marriage, at least from my experience.

20:40.094 --> 20:49.168
There's a lot of feeling leading up to it, a lot of feeling after it, but the thing itself is downright scary because you have to stand up there and they ask you questions.

20:49.208 --> 20:50.770
They don't ask you, how do you feel?

20:51.138 --> 20:53.041
or what have you been doing lately?

20:53.322 --> 20:55.104
No, they're all volitional questions.

20:56.326 --> 20:59.251
Do you take this woman to be your wedded wife?

21:02.196 --> 21:02.536
I do.

21:03.979 --> 21:06.503
You said, you might want to try that a little better.

21:06.543 --> 21:08.205
You know, she's going to be with you forever.

21:08.346 --> 21:08.666
I do.

21:09.087 --> 21:09.367
Okay.

21:10.008 --> 21:11.611
And do you receive this man?

21:12.172 --> 21:12.873
Yes, I do.

21:13.614 --> 21:13.935
Okay.

21:14.476 --> 21:15.417
You see where you get that?

21:15.517 --> 21:18.482
Well, imagine that it's Christ.

21:18.850 --> 21:24.238
and you standing at Christ and you standing at the front of the church, and God the Father is conducting this ceremony.

21:25.299 --> 21:29.786
And he says, son, do you take this sinner?

21:29.806 --> 21:32.710
And he says, I do.

21:32.830 --> 21:34.012
