21:35.615 --> 21:38.238
And sinner, do you take this Savior?

21:40.221 --> 21:40.722
I do.

21:42.530 --> 21:44.593
Now, this is what Paul is referring to here.

21:44.713 --> 21:49.479
Not concerned about a moment in time or being able to describe the details or whatever it might be.

21:49.779 --> 21:51.081
Don't get paralyzed by that.

21:51.141 --> 22:01.154
Spurgeon said, our inability to describe the exact experience of our physical birth does not call in question the reality of our existence.

22:01.535 --> 22:04.699
So don't go away and stress over that.

22:05.260 --> 22:09.025
But we recognize that if you say to somebody, are you married?

22:09.065 --> 22:10.066
And they say, I don't know.

22:11.586 --> 22:15.951
There's something seriously up with the person or the marriage or everything.

22:17.773 --> 22:21.797
There is therefore now no condemnation for those who like spiritual things.

22:22.258 --> 22:22.458
No.

22:22.838 --> 22:26.762
There is therefore now no condemnation for those who are enthusiastic and going to church.

22:26.882 --> 22:27.063
No.

22:27.483 --> 22:30.627
There is therefore now no condemnation and those who got baptized.

22:30.747 --> 22:31.608
No.

22:31.648 --> 22:33.029
Run through it anywhere you want.

22:33.049 --> 22:39.096
The only no condemnation now is for those who are in Christ Jesus.

22:39.836 --> 22:41.298
And what has he done?

22:41.922 --> 22:44.384
He has set us free.

22:44.444 --> 22:49.389
The law pronounces a curse upon us because we have broken the law.

22:50.290 --> 22:59.219
And the law then exercises a power over us to paralyze us and confront us all the time without which we'd leave us in the dust.

22:59.919 --> 23:03.163
And in Jesus, we have been set free.

23:03.223 --> 23:05.185
This is what he has done.

23:05.685 --> 23:08.308
The law of the Spirit has set you free.

23:08.348 --> 23:10.770
God in Jesus

23:11.234 --> 23:17.040
has accomplished what the law was absolutely unable to do.

23:17.060 --> 23:25.990
The law, he's written about this in the previous chapters, the law is holy, but is unable to make us holy.

23:27.051 --> 23:32.377
The law is righteous, but it cannot justify the ungodly.

23:32.397 --> 23:38.684
And in this work, you will notice, as you read the text, that the Trinity is involved.

23:39.004 --> 23:40.946
The Father plans it.

23:41.154 --> 23:45.259
the sun procures it, and the Holy Spirit applies us.

23:46.200 --> 23:49.024
And he says, this has been done by Jesus.

23:49.084 --> 24:01.338
For God has done with the law, weakened by the flesh, could not do by sending his own son in the likeness of sinful flesh and for sin, and he condemns sin in the flesh.

24:02.280 --> 24:08.627
Now, when the Bible uses flesh there, and the NIVR, remember, uses a different word, I think flesh is better.

24:09.248 --> 24:10.930
What it's referring to

24:11.042 --> 24:22.361
is human nature, human nature as human nature, corrupted and directed and controlled by sin.

24:24.464 --> 24:27.790
Otherwise, you can't make sense of verse seven.

24:28.431 --> 24:30.675
We might as well mention it now in case we never get to it.

24:30.955 --> 24:36.104
For the mind that is said on the flesh is hostile to God, it does not submit to God's law.

24:36.244 --> 24:37.586
Indeed, it cannot.

24:37.986 --> 24:41.130
For those who are in the flesh cannot please God."

24:42.913 --> 24:45.076
That's the answer incidentally to the question.

24:45.336 --> 24:59.416
Why is it that when people come out on the open sea with us and see the splendor of everything and the magnificence of the storm and the final calming of it and the trees and the mountains and the geology and everything, they don't just bow down and say, oh, what a mighty God we serve.

24:59.817 --> 25:00.498
Why don't they?

25:01.359 --> 25:06.546
Because after all, God's nature has been revealed to us in this.

25:06.946 --> 25:09.149
And it is revealed to us in our conscience.

25:09.650 --> 25:11.893
The answer is, they can't.

25:13.335 --> 25:17.660
Because those who are in the flesh cannot please God.

25:20.204 --> 25:23.148
You see, this is why we need the gospel.

25:23.488 --> 25:26.232
Because if we could please God, there's no need for a Savior.

25:26.993 --> 25:30.397
If all we have to do is just look around and say, well, that seems like a good idea to me.

25:31.399 --> 25:36.786
God has said this son, you will notice in the likeness of sinful flesh.

25:37.314 --> 25:56.460
In the likeness of sinful flesh, God has sent His Son in a manner that brought Him into the closest relationship to sinful humanity, that it was possible for Him to come without becoming sinful Himself.

25:58.023 --> 26:01.527
He's true human and yet sinless.

26:03.009 --> 26:03.951
And why has He come?

26:04.491 --> 26:06.354
Well, Jesus has come into the world

26:06.434 --> 26:09.077
to deal with sin, to deal with sin.

26:10.239 --> 26:14.585
Someone was asking me, not so long ago about Joel Osteen, they said, well, what do you think about it?

26:14.605 --> 26:17.949
And I said, he's got one of the nicest smiles I ever saw in television.

26:18.430 --> 26:22.855
I mean, if I could learn to smile like him, I think I would be making progress.

26:23.576 --> 26:31.026
I said, but I've heard him often in a talk show say, well, I don't like to talk about sin.

26:31.298 --> 26:36.103
I like to talk, and I'm going to be fine, and give me fine, and 10 sin.

26:36.143 --> 26:39.386
I got to get to my accent by saying, fine, I'll be fine.

26:39.926 --> 26:42.909
And I told, I told her, I said, well, okay, that's fine.

26:42.929 --> 26:44.030
I hear that.

26:44.871 --> 26:46.313
But that's a real problem, isn't it?

26:47.954 --> 26:53.119
You know, because how do you have, I guess you wouldn't want to talk about condemnation either.

26:53.139 --> 26:55.261
War judgment.

26:57.103 --> 27:00.146
What are the fact that we can please God in our own

27:01.474 --> 27:05.980
or meet God on our own terms or in our own time.

27:10.185 --> 27:11.647
You know, Jesus came to deal with sin.

27:12.147 --> 27:13.549
Can you imagine the situation?

27:13.609 --> 27:15.251
I bet you have.

27:17.153 --> 27:20.598
So Jesus is in a house and he's teaching.

27:21.639 --> 27:28.768
Because remember, he said that he came to teach, came to preach the gospel, repent the kingdom of God is at hand, repent to believe the good good.

27:29.068 --> 27:30.450
And he's in the house and he's teaching.

27:31.618 --> 27:36.204
And a group of guys got one of their friends whose legs didn't work.

27:37.386 --> 27:40.470
I took him on a bed and brought him to the house.

27:41.632 --> 27:42.553
Couldn't get in the house.

27:42.934 --> 27:44.296
Couldn't get in through the vestibule.

27:44.836 --> 27:45.918
Couldn't do anything at all.

27:46.519 --> 27:48.241
If I'd been there, I'd say, well, let's just go home.

27:48.301 --> 27:49.703
We'll come back again another time.

27:49.723 --> 27:51.385
But no, these fellows were creative.

27:51.846 --> 27:53.288
And so they said, we'll go through the roof.

27:53.849 --> 27:55.231
And you remember this story?

27:55.251 --> 27:57.714
And they go through the roof and they let the man down.

27:57.986 --> 27:58.947
What an interruption.

27:58.967 --> 28:01.791
Can you imagine if something happened to you and a guy landed here on a bed?

28:02.452 --> 28:08.439
I mean, do you remember Jesus opening mine?

28:10.341 --> 28:11.803
He looked at the man and what did he say?

28:12.484 --> 28:15.528
Son, your sins are forgiven.

28:17.070 --> 28:17.310
What?

28:19.132 --> 28:24.118
Can you imagine if you had brought this guy all the way on?

28:24.699 --> 28:26.962
And Jesus says, your sins are forgiven?

28:28.226 --> 28:30.128
We said, no, we didn't bring him here for sins.

28:30.989 --> 28:32.211
We brought him here for his legs.

28:33.573 --> 28:35.755
We didn't come for an invisible forgiveness.

28:36.576 --> 28:38.078
We came for a physical healing.

28:38.839 --> 28:40.661
This is what the man really needs.

28:42.844 --> 28:47.750
Oh, Jesus fixed his legs, but he dealt with what the man really needs.

28:49.172 --> 28:51.074
He needed a new heart.

28:51.094 --> 28:52.115
He needed a Savior.

28:52.976 --> 28:54.258
He needed change.

28:55.298 --> 28:58.741
And the Pharisees would take who can forgive sins, but God alone.

29:00.803 --> 29:07.470
He says to him, well, what do you think is easier to say to him, son, your sins are forgiven, or pick up your bed and go home?

29:08.791 --> 29:13.815
From one perspective, it's easier to say your sins are forgiven, because after all, how would anybody know?

29:14.096 --> 29:15.137
How would you verify it?

29:15.297 --> 29:16.158
Your sins are forgiven.

29:16.358 --> 29:16.978
Have a great day.

29:18.520 --> 29:22.043
But if you're going to say, pick up your bed and walk, you've got a challenge right there.

29:23.925 --> 29:24.946
And you remember what he said?

29:25.410 --> 29:32.318
in order that you might know that the Son of Man has authority on earth to forgive sins.

29:32.638 --> 29:35.561
I say to you, pick up your bed and go home.

29:35.922 --> 29:39.065
And the man picked up his bed immediately and walked out.

29:39.526 --> 29:40.607
Now, what was Jesus doing?

29:41.248 --> 29:53.682
He was putting his finger on not only that man's, but he was putting his finger on every man and every woman's greatest need, the need to be reconciled to God.

29:54.274 --> 29:56.418
They need to have their conscience cleansed.

29:56.999 --> 30:10.283
They need to be set free from the bondage to religious orthodoxy that has led them to redundancy so that they might live in the blissful reality of the freedom that is theirs in the Lord Jesus.

30:11.445 --> 30:16.754
The righteous requirement, he says, of the law would then be fulfilled

30:16.930 --> 30:20.957
in those who walk not according to the flesh, but according to the Spirit.

30:21.217 --> 30:24.262
The righteous requirement of the law might be fulfilled in us."

30:27.007 --> 30:28.730
People get this wrong all the time, don't they?

30:28.750 --> 30:30.713
Because I hear them in local Bible studies.

30:30.733 --> 30:32.556
They say, oh, yeah, but we're not under law.

30:32.596 --> 30:33.838
We're under grace.

30:33.879 --> 30:34.880
The law is finished now.

30:34.900 --> 30:35.962
That was the Old Testament.

30:36.202 --> 30:38.306
We're New Testament people.

30:38.326 --> 30:40.690
Yeah, you're Old Testament and New Testament people.

30:41.218 --> 30:47.047
We're no longer under the law in the way that it brings a curse and pressure upon us, as if some are another.

30:47.267 --> 30:50.052
We could climb up a ladder to acceptance with God.

30:50.432 --> 30:59.526
We're no longer under that, but we are under the jurisdiction and direction of the law of God to live a holy life.

31:00.207 --> 31:02.391
The Westminster Confession of Faith helps with it.

31:02.471 --> 31:09.842
It says this, the Spirit of Christ subdues and enables the will of man

31:10.178 --> 31:18.729
to do freely and cheerfully that which the will of God revealed in the law requires to be done.

31:21.252 --> 31:29.202
The spirit of Christ subdues the good that I, the bad that I don't want to do.

31:29.442 --> 31:32.627
It is the spirit of God that works to subdue.

31:32.687 --> 31:38.514
And then to do the good that I ought to do

31:39.266 --> 31:47.698
It then enables not to do it reluctantly or grudgingly, but freely and cheerfully.

31:49.160 --> 31:54.588
And this, you see, is all part of the amazing package in Christ.

31:56.571 --> 31:59.174
If you need to think it's true, then that's good and you must.

31:59.254 --> 32:00.016
And we must.

32:01.077 --> 32:05.263
The Ten Commandments were given to Israel after Israel was freed.

32:06.385 --> 32:07.346
They were freed.

32:08.994 --> 32:12.219
And then they were told how freedom was to be enjoyed.

32:13.902 --> 32:17.968
Redemption precedes the requirements.

32:19.130 --> 32:22.175
God delivers, and then he demands.

32:23.837 --> 32:37.298
And the lives that bear evidence to this are there for us in the fourth verse, who walk not according to the flesh,

32:37.602 --> 32:39.785
but according to the Spirit.

32:41.447 --> 32:43.169
I can tell by the way you walk.

32:43.770 --> 32:44.831
That's the song, isn't it?

32:45.372 --> 32:48.495
I can tell by the way you walk, you got so old, baby.

32:48.836 --> 32:52.120
You go, so you can tell a lot of other way a person walks.

32:52.140 --> 32:57.286
They strut or they're stooped or they're cool or whatever it is.

32:57.306 --> 33:01.371
He said, well, look how they walk.

33:01.391 --> 33:06.738
Well, he says, there's a Christian walk who walked not according to the flesh.

33:09.250 --> 33:15.176
You see, the contrast couldn't actually be any clearer than the way in which it is put here.

33:16.077 --> 33:24.024
For those who live according to the flesh set their minds on the things of the flesh, but those who live according to the Spirit set their minds on the things of the Spirit.

33:25.185 --> 33:29.089
We in Christ, we now live according to the Spirit.

33:29.950 --> 33:38.098
Not only in redemption, not only have we been reconciled to God, but the Spirit of God has come to live within us.

33:39.042 --> 33:42.988
that we are dwelling place of God by the Holy Spirit.

33:43.749 --> 33:51.421
And therefore, it is the renewing work of the Holy Spirit, the free and work of the Holy Spirit, that enables us to do what God requires for us to do.

33:51.461 --> 34:03.761
The flesh, human nature, is hopeless, is hostile, and is helpless.

34:05.904 --> 34:07.186
It's hopeless.

34:08.706 --> 34:12.472
Men and women without God and without a hope in the world.

34:16.218 --> 34:18.481
Hostile, hostile.

34:20.725 --> 34:25.132
The mind that is said on the flesh is hostile to God.

34:28.898 --> 34:36.690
You know, I think I've told this story before, but I was playing golf in California and there were guys that on the golf course I didn't know and I got put together with a group

34:37.090 --> 34:39.853
Some of the jokes would make a sailor blush.

34:39.873 --> 34:46.782
And after a long while of this going on, at a moment, on a tee, one of the men said, and so what do you do?

34:49.004 --> 34:52.489
And I said, oh, I was almost embarrassed to say it.

34:52.509 --> 34:53.610
I said, I'm a pastor.

34:54.491 --> 34:55.773
There's long silence.

34:56.634 --> 35:02.241
And then one of the guys broke the silence by saying, so how's business for you?

35:04.744 --> 35:06.706
I said, oh, it's excellent.

35:07.074 --> 35:07.915
Excellent.

35:07.935 --> 35:09.958
There's no shortage of sinners.

35:10.579 --> 35:16.509
No shortage of sinners.

35:17.049 --> 35:22.598
And we teed off and went down the fairway and I was, I don't want to say I was in the middle of the fairway.

35:22.678 --> 35:24.080
It probably was in the middle of the rough.

35:24.120 --> 35:35.538
But one of these little guys, the smallest of the group, the one who'd been telling most of the jokes, came up to me on his cart and he said, hey, I don't like what you said right there.

35:36.290 --> 35:38.132
I said, so sorry, what'd I say?

35:38.152 --> 35:39.633
He said, well, you were calling me a sinner.

35:40.354 --> 35:41.175
You're calling me a sinner.

35:42.135 --> 35:44.097
I said, well, I wasn't actually calling you a sinner.

35:44.117 --> 35:45.399
But he said, yeah, you were.

35:45.619 --> 35:46.119
Here you were.

35:46.139 --> 35:48.201
And he said, you need to know.

35:48.602 --> 35:49.502
I am not a sinner.

35:50.263 --> 35:50.944
That's what he said.

35:51.204 --> 35:52.065
I am not a sinner.

35:53.726 --> 35:54.867
This is up in 1,000 Oaks.

35:55.128 --> 35:55.948
I'm not a sinner.

35:56.269 --> 36:03.155
I said, well, I am delighted to meet you because there's only one other person that I ever heard of who made that claim.

36:03.776 --> 36:04.637
And he was so stupid.

36:04.657 --> 36:06.258
He said, and who was that?

36:07.490 --> 36:11.655
I said, Jesus of Nazareth, he goes, well, if you're going to put it that way.

36:11.935 --> 36:13.257
And then he went off on his car.

36:15.439 --> 36:23.748
But at the end of the round, because I didn't want to make an enemy of the man at the end of the round, as we got a chance to talk, I said, hey, listen, do you want to know how I know so much about sinners?

36:24.449 --> 36:25.090
He said, yeah.

36:25.490 --> 36:26.692
I said, because I am a sinner.

36:28.173 --> 36:35.762
I said, I don't have to look further than my shaving mirror in the opening part of the day to see a sinner.

36:37.282 --> 36:38.504
He said, well, I don't understand.

36:38.604 --> 36:45.294
And then I told him, Jesus came to save sinners.

36:45.314 --> 36:47.678
And the only people he saves are actually sinners.

36:48.860 --> 36:54.369
It's only bad people that go to heaven, bad people who are saved by people.

36:56.432 --> 36:58.435
He said, we'll have to talk about that some more.

36:59.517 --> 37:01.319
I haven't had the chance to talk to him anymore.

37:01.400 --> 37:05.586
I often wonder if when he's driving on the freeway in LA,

37:06.146 --> 37:09.531
if he ever heard this funny little Scottish voice.

37:11.153 --> 37:17.942
Now the flesh is there, cannot the spirit, the spirit.

37:21.427 --> 37:23.690
We set our minds on the things of the spirit.

37:25.152 --> 37:34.866
Our time, our talents, our treasures are now to be governed and directed by God's word.

37:36.386 --> 37:45.900
It is in the spirit that hostility is replaced by harmony, that instead of death, there is life and peace.

37:47.162 --> 37:56.836
I mean, even just to sing the two songs that we've already sung is to sing out, essentially, the whole thrust of what Paul is saying in these verses.

37:58.238 --> 38:01.923
We're set free from the law of sin and death.

38:02.684 --> 38:03.826
We're set free

38:04.290 --> 38:16.830
as a way of accepting before God, but we're obliged to keep it as the way of holiness in living for God.

38:19.113 --> 38:32.594
The contrast is there, two kinds of people, two differing mindsets, two resulting lifestyles, and two ultimate destinies.

38:37.186 --> 38:37.967
What's that song?

38:38.007 --> 38:40.390
I've got my mind stayed on you.

38:40.450 --> 38:42.972
I've got my mind stayed on you.

38:43.032 --> 39:06.418
It's a reminder to me, at least, that our minds do matter, that the things that we contemplate, the dreams we pursue, the hopes that we hold out for our children and for our grandchildren, are either going to be framed in a way that is antithetical to all that God desires for us.

39:06.978 --> 39:08.520
Or they're going to be framed by that.

39:10.943 --> 39:21.637
Goldsworthy Australian theologian helped me greatly along the journey of the last few years.

39:22.438 --> 39:24.961
And this quote I've had in my notes for a long time.

39:25.582 --> 39:35.474
This is where he says, and I'll end with this, only the message that another true and obedient human being has come on our behalf.

39:36.770 --> 39:52.686
that he has lived for us the kind of life we should live but can't, that he has paid fully the punishment we deserve for the life we do live but shouldn't.

39:55.008 --> 40:04.498
Only this message can give assurance that we have peace with God through our Lord Jesus Christ.

40:06.050 --> 40:22.569
Only this message that the historical Jesus is the living Lord, that the Christ who died is the Christ who lives, that the Christ who intercedes is the Christ who will come.

40:22.590 --> 40:33.202
And he comes for those who are ready to meet him and the privilege of conference time like this in the company of one another.

40:33.730 --> 40:50.273
is an opportunity to stir one another up in these things, and perhaps just to be reminded of the simple but profound reality with which we begin, that there is no condemnation to them that are in Christ Jesus.

40:52.316 --> 40:54.499
What will separate us from the love of God?

40:55.540 --> 40:56.462
Death won't do it.

40:58.805 --> 40:59.065
Why?

40:59.646 --> 41:02.610
Because it is an ontological impossibility.

41:03.842 --> 41:09.009
to be separated from Christ, now that we are placed in Him.

41:12.554 --> 41:14.016
We say, I don't really feel this.

41:16.039 --> 41:16.579
It's okay.

41:18.141 --> 41:19.083
Fly the instruments.

41:22.167 --> 41:26.252
Apply your mind and let your heart catch up.

41:28.596 --> 41:29.096
Believe it.

41:30.358 --> 41:31.119
Lay hold of it.

41:31.159 --> 41:33.362
Take it yourself.

41:33.826 --> 41:43.315
Look at yourself in the mirror and say, what a wonder is this, that there is no condemnation to me in Christ Jesus.

41:44.537 --> 41:49.602
Not because of anything I'm doing or have done, but because of everything he has done.

41:51.924 --> 42:02.034
Lord, we do pray that the words of our mouths, the words of my mouth, the meditation of our hearts may be found acceptable

42:02.786 --> 42:05.429
in your sight, your strength, and our redeemer.

42:06.690 --> 42:23.126
Pray that anything that is unhelpful or untrue might be banished from our recollection, and all that is of yourself may find a resting place as we go through the balance of the day and into the balance of the week.

42:23.987 --> 42:31.634
